    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund increased sick pay for community carers during Covid-19 outbreak",
        "additional_details": "As carers we are all out doing essential jobs during this pandemic, but if we fall ill with Covid through doing so there is little to no support, \u00a380 per week in Statutory Sick Pay doesn\u2019t cut it. We are taking risks daily to provide care, yet when we become ill there\u2019s little or no financial help for us.\r\n \r\nThe Government should fund increased sick pay for community carers so that they do not have to subsists on Statutory Sick Pay if they fall ill during the outbreak.",
        "background": "The Government should fund increased sick pay for frontline community carers that fall ill during the Covid-19 outbreak.",
